Date: Mon, 23 Jul 2001 20:04:11 -0400
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AP Online 23 Jul 2001 17:34 EDT [edited

Florida Man Tests Positive for West Nile
---------------------------------
TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- A Florida man has tested positive for West
Nile virus, the state's first known case of a human contracting the
potentially deadly disease. Officials at the Department of Health said
Monday they believe the patient has the virus, although federal
officials are also testing him. The man, more than 50 years old, is
hospitalized in intensive care.
The disease usually causes only flu-like symptoms, although it can
kill older people or those with weakened immune systems. It has killed
9 people in New York and New Jersey in the last 2 years.
The virus has been found in birds in 7 north Florida counties since it
was first detected in early July [2001. A horse died from the
disease.
